Material Information Summary (ASX:TSO - Exploration Results Announcement)

  • Key Drilling Results at Ternera (El Zorro Gold Project, Chile):
  • Southern Extension (outside current MRE boundary):
    • 63.97m @ 1.26g/t Au (including 9.34m @ 6.60g/t Au)
    • 51.32m @ 1.13g/t Au (including 11.10m @ 2.57g/t Au)
    • 39.40m @ 1.23g/t Au (including 10.87m @ 2.65g/t Au)

  • Northern Shallow Zone:

    • 8.84m @ 1.65g/t Au (including 1.40m @ 5.67g/t Au)

  • Resource Context:

  • Results confirm expansion potential of the 1.3Moz MRE, with mineralization open along strike.

  • Southern zone lies 30m outside current pit shell (US$1,800/oz optimized).

  • Next Steps:

  • Ongoing drilling to define extensions for upcoming MRE update (targeting inclusion of southern/northern zones).
  • Two rigs operating 24/7; full capacity restored after rig replacement.

No capital raising, trading halt, or financial metrics disclosed. Focused on resource growth.

Summary of Material Information:

  • Contract Expansion with TPAC:
  • Scaled from Arizona pilot to full value-based agreement covering 15,000 Medicare lives (potential to scale further).
  • Revenue streams:
    • Guaranteed PMPM fee (~US$5 per member per month).
    • RPM reimbursements at ~US$70 PPPM (30% patient conversion target → ~US$3M p.a.).
    • Performance bonuses tied to CMS quality savings.
  • Term: 1-year initial + annual renewals (60-day termination notice).

  • Growth potential: TPAC targeting 100,000 Medicare lives within 3 years.

  • Strategic Significance:

  • Second major U.S. partnership in 2025 (follows Evolent/HIPA MSSP).

  • Positions Vitasora as a leader in value-based care solutions under CMS mandates.

  • Pipeline Outlook: Additional contract wins expected in coming months.

Material Information Summary

Key Highlights:

  • Challenger Project Mineral Resources Update (JORC 2012):
  • Total Resources: 223koz Au (9.56Mt @ 0.72 g/t Au).
    • Main Open Pit: 69.6koz Au (0.64Mt @ 3.39 g/t Au).
    • Challenger West Open Pit: 11.6koz Au (0.03Mt @ 10.6 g/t Au).
    • Underground (1,000 – 900mRL): 21.9koz Au (0.17Mt @ 3.98 g/t Au).
    • Tailings Facilities (TSF1 & TSF2): 107.3koz Au (8.33Mt @ 0.4 g/t Au).
  • Total Barton Gold JORC Resources: 1.9Moz Au (73.0Mt @ 0.79 g/t Au).
  • Silver Resources (Tunkillia only): 3.1Moz Ag (34.5Mt @ 2.80 g/t Ag).

Commercialisation Pathway (Stage 1):

  • Immediate Focus: Higher-grade tailings and open-pit material adjacent to Central Gawler Mill.
  • Next Steps:
  • Re-extend Challenger Underground Model (below 900mRL).
  • Feasibility Studies & Reserves Estimate by end of 2025, targeting initial production by end of 2026.
  • Capital & Mining Studies for recommissioning Central Gawler Mill.

Metallurgical & Processing Insights:

  • Tailings (TSF1 & TSF2): Preliminary test work indicates potential 70% gold recovery through regrinding.
  • Gold Price Sensitivity: Assumed A$3,500/oz for cut-off calculations.

Trading & Valuation Impact

  • Potential Near-Term Production: Reactivating the fully permitted Central Gawler Mill could accelerate cash flow.
  • Resource Expansion Potential: Further drilling may upgrade underground and inferred resources.
  • Strategic Value: Exposure to a secured infrastructure advantage in the Gawler Craton.

No material capital raising or corporate action disclosed.
